		<geography>
			<locationOfOperationSupplyOrProduction location="CN">
				<descriptionOfRestrictions xml:lang="en">This study performs a life-cycle assessment for a photovoltaic (PV) system with multi-crystalline silicon (multi-Si) modules in China</descriptionOfRestrictions>
				<descriptionOfRestrictions xml:lang="zh">本研究对中国采用多晶硅组件的光伏系统进行了生命周期评估</descriptionOfRestrictions>
			</locationOfOperationSupplyOrProduction>
		</geography>
		<technology>
			<technologicalApplicability xml:lang="en">The multi-crystalline silicon (multi-Si) ingot casting process described here is employed for the production of solar-grade silicon ingots, which are subsequently sliced into wafers, fabricated into cells, and assembled into modules for use in photovoltaic (PV) systems. These PV systems utilize multi-Si modules predominantly for the conversion of solar energy into electricity, and are essential components of solar farms, rooftop installations, and various other applications that harness solar power for electricity generation.</technologicalApplicability>
			<technologicalApplicability xml:lang="zh">此处描述的多晶硅铸锭过程用于生产太阳能级硅锭，然后将其切割成硅片，制成电池，并组装成用于光伏（PV）系统的组件。这些光伏系统主要使用多晶硅组件将太阳能转换为电能，是太阳能农场、屋顶装置以及各种利用太阳能发电的其他应用的基本组成部分。</technologicalApplicability>
			<referenceToTechnologyFlowDiagrammOrPicture type="source data set" refObjectId="7506d463-2654-e8c5-5be0-f5ac10ac3546" uri="../sources/7506d463-2654-e8c5-5be0-f5ac10ac3546.xml">
				<common:shortDescription xml:lang="en">GSvEbT284otn6Uxk366cUzLpnKe.png</common:shortDescription>
			</referenceToTechnologyFlowDiagrammOrPicture>
		</technology>
	</processInformation>
